@Rochedale68: Feel free to ignore countries where measures that enhance proportional representation and routine minority governance works just fine.

FPTP alienates wide swaths of the electorate and leads to insane outcomes, such as in the 1993 election, when the federal Conservative Party landed only 2 out of 295 seats, despite garnering 16% of the vote (which, in a perfectly proportional system [not saying that's possible], would have garnered around 47 seats).

The system can be improved.
